HB 281 Original 2026 Regular Session Green
Abstract: Requires automobile insurers to provide motor vehicle liability coverage
information to third-party claimants or their attorneys upon receipt of a written
request. Outlines procedures, addresses confidentiality considerations and
establishes provisions for retroactive application.
Proposed law requires automobile insurers to provide liability policy limits to third-party
insurance claimants or their attorney within 30 days of receipt of a written request from a
claimant or his attorney.
Proposed law requires insurers to disclose the following:
(1) The name of the insurer.
(2) The name of each insured associated with the vehicle involved in the accident.
(3) An indication of coverage limits or a statement indicating that the insurer did not issue
a policy that provides coverage for the automobile accident.
